message:
Oh, don't even try Economist. You're incompetent enough when you deal with things you allegedly "know", like economics and international relations.

Your articles on tennis and rugby are even more painful. The reason that the All Blacks are the best side is because:

(1) they have a fantastic, centralised coaching system where all the clubs are under direction from the New Zealand Rugby Union, who ensure all the players are working towards eventually being All Blacks;
(2) it is essentially the only sport they play in New Zealand (bar a few people playing cricket and rugby league);
(3) excellence breeds excellence and all their players grow up playing with other great players, and against Australians and South Africans who are, historically, the two next best rugby nations;
(4) they have a coaching system whereupon the future coach serves as an understudy as assistant coach for years before they are promoted in order to ensure continuity;
(5) the standards of the rest of the world have dropped—since about 2007 Australia and South Africa have been averagely coached and lacked depth, South Africa is further hamstrung by political interference, and the Northern Hemisphere is never that strong comparatively.

I truly believe the side of about 2003-2007 was stronger than that today, but the difference was that they were more arrogant, the culture was worse and Australia and South Africa were stronger.

You can put up all the stats and graphs in the world, but it still doesn't mean  you have a clue.

